Account.docs: An Account represents an account with an insurance carrier and includes high-level account information (e.g. name) and any Policy objects associated with the Account.

Policy.docs: A Policy represents a specific policy associated with an Account and includes high-level policy information (e.g. policy number) and any children objects (e.g., coverages) associated with the policy.

UserPhone.docs: User's phone number in E.164 format.

properties.docs: User's phone number in E.164 format.

User.docs: User to attach to Ignition session. If user is set, unique `id` must be provided.

Success.docs: Indicates whether the operation was performed successfully.

ErrorMessage.docs: Provides a reason for why the operation failed, if available.

endpoints.docs:
Exchange an authorization code for an access token. Ignition returns an authCode as a query parameter at the redirectUrl upon successful completion of the Ignition flow.

Auth codes are ephemeral and expire after 10 minutes, while accessTokens do not expire.

The Get Account method will return an Account object including high-level account information (e.g., name) and any children objects (e.g., Policies) associated with the Account. Please note that this method will NOT refresh the Account object.

The Get Policy method returns a Policy object including high-level policy information (e.g., policy number) and any children objects (e.g., Coverages) associated with the Policy. Please note that this method will NOT refresh the Policy object.
The Get Carriers method returns an array of Carrier objects.
